outcome.review_summary: Excellent implementation of REST-based models. The feature is complete with well-structured config models (RestAuthConfig, RestModelConfig), a clean RestModel class with dot-path request/response mapping, proper integration into ModelEvaluator with a dedicated _register_rest_model path, and thorough session cleanup. 30 well-organized tests cover helpers, config validation, auth types, request/response mapping, error handling, and edge cases. PR description is detailed and clear, docstrings are comprehensive, lint is clean, and all 1290 tests pass. The requests dependency was correctly added to pyproject.toml and exports are properly wired through __init__.py.
